[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring GroovyShell options**\n\nI’m considering whether to use GroovyShell, but there's a public factor to think about. It doesn’t provide direct reflection, so I might need to add a test dependency since Groovy is transitive. If I write a Java test using GroovyShell or InvokerHelper, I’ll be able to invoke static methods by name. However, it seems like the active call would still be class$. I’m trying to clarify how the helper public API works in this context.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_00cbb9a91a538cd1016a27e5280cd88196bf7dfe1d0d91eb86\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJ-U-Yw1ZRZLRL-LIglSSGUr5J6E6F-sHT4_XVBSkOERomCDhAZvLxChHPMT1_FYz9Uo7EQrq3WScVz1Uiz0BO7xrcVQuToJ_wPg9TyWQpanFeA4d8ONCPDBPkyui6pBhvDRVO145XtKGVFFU3Qn88L_R3sxVo5CqJrrrV66z49eXuuGW9Zlq1SgFQozEYg3Qof6MRIMh_8594A9su5Q0voxF0oYKIqgw5e5-6y68lIW5cRXIbiJQoFQV_5BZ-5T-ERulbmQWsTNFUrGi9EMizQbF9wYIwWf7nDWpJCVB_Sn2DVWs1WqFnGgliuQgYO3hTxov85xflMO9itaF3hsVvY2qjsXyEuMp8H3jk4IGfLqD_8iPflqgFyYXvgrpHDAJi_CR9OmF7_xibWwUFMXP3aZgklj0g3XFOTpTTyyI-yY3K4sGD8HuTn9YUpnYGvt_zIMjfiYln0Fr7I_urA6iVJt5bW7_zcACbpZPB1HisazwK9KyjlAaMWncaXrlY03uSDnF1TKeBmchlxI7kRKJqMmwpqzLD130ldR5cw15QW8hROH6LRJs4HEjzsd9HRqI0VJwDLO-kz151HK65_OflBvS10yH6eFbJ7K4CqI79bo4SUQircQfMliGKRLetfnQJYYeX9o5b4wUvnHDvAFAUC2xRAzgdgzyU1Th_o2rUkPqWbjGHT3ZL6g-nYrZDyx1z5BdXCe1IY0yppuY5wq0aAwzjx4p7zIVN0disVSn7rPB3H7yA2TTSYd95pVSYQZhYTpuzPZeQuxp3OY43uSYoLs1UFY1TJHwzoXpp__kqqgmigwGOpQ5TTSgNDLx9WvHmxhmBFVtXYoHD0ZQV8U56fdiZUPUvMjbyn-rVXr4A7Yz-CeVsXzA8UQEnkqSDUnPqN3y0VSqxL1RV1zNpNFan8W-AXYPp6dqrtjJBfURDDAWfx71bPxqaBrN40_ZUzqx6K0cKykUAYdShHVOXuXc0CxK68NG1mKJGukTo9bXL8ISBhwCVyFgS_V8mFtZCdDK83mDi1QNLDqXjbyqsqwl7ifgb0ZgQtTHEAuD_TW4nQG-h0o5_KLklEneYiQ-5WreewrUDkMXhrJvueUxtUvnXHt9MxF6VLvdyMih0lhB-726zbglHw66J2RatZWdS5MvnEfy70MFlcJOixx4cTs0q33gJuS5r43EtnU0vHiMrJfCngZC6YT6aVMMbO5OKoTQBWDs5HtSgYiM80lYRo_ZfsGQpPY-0-NvApExmIFD1kQ